Package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.binding.model.property

Interface IBoundInstance

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IInstance, IModelElement
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IBoundAssemblyInstance, IBoundFieldInstance, IBoundFieldValueInstance, IBoundFlagInstance, IBoundNamedInstance, IBoundNamedModelInstance
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAssemblyDefinitionAssemblyProperty, AbstractAssemblyProperty, AbstractFieldDefinitionFieldProperty, AbstractFieldProperty, AbstractNamedModelProperty, AbstractNamedProperty, AbstractProperty, DefaultAssemblyProperty, DefaultFieldProperty, DefaultFieldValueProperty, DefaultFlagProperty, RelativeAssemblyDefinitionAssemblyProperty, RelativeFieldDefinitionFieldProperty, RootDefinitionAssemblyProperty
    public interface IBoundInstance
extends IInstance
    Represents a property on a Java class that is bound to a Metaschema object (i.e., Assembly, Field, or Flag). A property has a field and associated getter and setter methods.

    Properties are bound to constructs in XML and JSON/YAML formats.

    In XML key characteristics of a property binding include:

    • The name and namespace of the property which will be used for the associated element or attribute.

    In JSON/YAML key characteristics of a property binding include:

    • A string-based key representing the field name of a JSON/YAML object
